title: Father of internet warns: Don't rush investments into A.I. just because ChatGPT is 'really cool'
description: "Father of the internet" and Google internet evangelist Vint Cerf warned entrepreneurs not to rush into making money from conversational AI.

title: Airbnb beats on profit and revenue, stock is up
description: Airbnb reported fourth-quarter earnings that beat analysts' expectations on top and bottom lines.

title: Biden taps Fed's Brainard, Bernstein for top economic jobs as part of White House reshuffle
description: The White House tapped Lael Brainard and Jared Bernstein to two critical roles shaping U.S. economic policy as the country grapples with high inflation.

title: Ford halts production and shipments of its electric F-150 Lightning due to potential battery issue
description: The production halt adds to ongoing "execution issues" detailed to investors earlier this month by Ford CEO Jim Farley.

title: Russian forces have relocated at least 6,000 Ukrainian children to camps since start of war, new report says
description: The allegations against Russia detailed in the report, such as the abduction or detention of Ukrainian children, may constitute war crimes.

title: The US, China spy balloon tensions are drifting into politics of the supply chain
description: The U.S-China trade relationship has endured Covid and tariffs. Now alleged spy balloons are giving industries like retail another reason to move manufacturing.

title: Germany rules out spending 'more and more money' as Europe hopes to avoid subsidy race with the U.S.
description: European Union officials have been embroiled in tense discussions over how to make the region more competitive.

title: Boeing orders, deliveries slip in January, before massive Air India jetliner sale
description: Boeing has been hesitant to ramp up plane production before stabilizing its supply chain.

title: Inflation rose 0.5% in January, more than expected and up 6.4% from a year ago
description: The consumer price index was expected to increase 0.4% in January from a month ago and 6.2% on an annual basis, according to Dow Jones.

title: Livestream shopping took China by storm. Now Amazon, TikTok and YouTube are betting the QVC-style pitches will take off in the U.S.
description: Despite huge success in China, livestream shopping has caught on slowly in the U.S., but Amazon, TikTok and YouTube are making big bets that's about to change.

title: Nikki Haley enters race for president as first challenger to Trump for the Republican nomination
description: Haley called for a new generation of leaders, saying Biden's record was "abysmal" and the "Washington establishment has failed us over and over and over again."

title: Tesla board member says Musk doesn't mind bankruptcy if a rival builds a better car: 'That's his philosophy'
description: Elon Musk remarked that he wouldn't mind Tesla going bankrupt, if it means a rival company builds a better car, according to a company board member.

title: Coca-Cola revenue rises in fourth quarter, fueled by higher prices
description: Coke said its unit case volume, which strips out the impact of currency and price changes, fell 1% in its fourth quarter.

title: Crypto markets on edge as U.S. regulatory crackdown on industry intensifies
description: Investors are digesting a number of major regulatory actions in the U.S., as authorities look to rein in the once free-wheeling cryptocurrency industry.

title: Singapore 2022 deficit set to be lower than expected; inflationary pressures persist
description: The Singapore government will be pumping in another S$3 billion to help households cope with the rising costs of living and GST hikes.

title: 'Think of the unthinkable': IMF chief warns world is a very different place after crises like Covid
description: IMF Managing Director Georgieva Kristalina said that, in the "shock-prone" world we live in, people need to be more agile and "think of the unthinkable."

title: Ford to cut 3,800 jobs in Europe in shift to electric vehicle production
description: Ford said it intends to cut 3,800 product development and administration jobs in Europe in the next three years.

title: Kazuo Ueda is set to become Japan's next central bank governor. Here's what it means
description: Ueda would replace current central bank chief Governor Haruhiko Kuroda, who was first appointed in March 2013. His current five-year term will end on April 8.

title: Promoting FTX was their side hustle. Now they’re left to pick up the pieces
description: FTX student ambassadors promoted the now bankrupt crypto exchange on their campuses to help expand it's customer base and lose funds when it collapsed.

title: Shut out from their top destinations, Chinese travelers are turning to other places
description: Visa difficulties and high-profile rows with South Korea and Japan are pushing many Chinese travelers to opt for vacations to Southeast Asia.

title: 'Fed is not your friend': Wells Fargo delivers warning ahead of key inflation report
description: Wells Fargo Securities' Michael Schumacher believes Fed policy is working against equity investors regardless of this week's inflation data outcome.

title: China's tech giants are launching ChatGPT clones — and Beijing is watching closely
description: Chinese technology giants from Alibaba to Baidu have announced their intentions to launch ChatGPT-style products.
